@node desc "Description"

This is a shared library which allows your existing terminal
(XEM compatible) to use Viewdata terminal emulation. To install
it, copy the relevant library to your libs: directory, or where
you usually put your XEM libraries.

Viewdata is used for home banking in the UK by certain banks,
and there are still a few BBSes out there that use it.
@endnode

@node conf "Configuration"
How you set the configuration will vary depending on the program
you are using, but there is only one option at the moment, and it
is always off.

  Capture to file:
    data received by the terminal is saved to a file.
@endnode

